I felt from day 1 that #AfterTheRain was a truly special song, but I always thought that it was meant to be a duet at its core.  @tenillearts has been one of my favorite voices in a town full of great ones for a while now and it was a no brainer to ask her to be a part of it. I couldn’t be more pumped and excited that she said yes. This one sure feels like magic now. Our version is out on 4.7.23. Link in bio to be one of the first to hear it ⚡️

Met this fella on my birthday 9 years ago. May 15, 2014. Had no idea then what kinda journey we’d be on together, but I can’t help but feel like it’s sorta all led to today.  There ain’t anything I can say about the guy that I haven’t already said, but I’ll say this. Every once in a while, someone comes along that defies everything. The rules, the odds, the naysayers, the pundits, and they do it THEIR way…unabashedly, without hesitation, and with the most authenticity imaginable. History remembers those people. @lukecombs is one of those - I just happen to get to call him a best friend.  I told him back in January that I think this album is his magnum opus (if you don’t know what it is, I put it in the last slide slide for ya haha) and that’s what this album is. It’s a work of art, it’s connection in it’s purest form, it’s a masterpiece, it’s something he and everyone that has a part in it can hang their hat on forever.  I’m damn proud to have wrote these 6 songs on it, and even prouder to do it with a dude who is one of the greatest artists our generation, but more importantly one of the best men I know.  What an album. Y’all go gas it #gettinold

My debut album “Spray Painted Line” turned 1 year old today! I’m still so proud of it and every song on it. Thank you to everyone who’s listened to it, spread the word, and took the time to message me about what it’s meant to you. I hope you found a little piece of yourself in it somewhere. Make no mistake though, I been back in the studio and we coming bigger and better than ever soon. Til then, what’s been your favorite song off of SPL?? Lemme know in the comments. Thank y’all! ⚡️

After almost 9 years of playing together, last night was @charlielance3 last show with us (til I talk him into playing again one day haha). There’s not enough space here to say all I want to say about the guy, but ill say this. Not only is Charlie one of the best musicians I’ve ever met, but he’s also one of the wisest, most intuitive, smartest, and caring people I’ve ever met.  More than that, he’s one of the best men, husbands, and fathers I’ve ever known and I’ve learned a whole lot about life from him. We’ve seen each other at our best and worst, we’ve laughed and cried together more than I could count, and have a whole lifetime of memories packed in the last decade.  After a while, a band starts to feel like a family, and Charlie has been like a brother to me for a long time now. Just wanted to say I feel really lucky to have gotten to chase this dream with him to my right for we long as I have.  Here’s to what’s next buddy, I’m real proud of you. Thanks for believing in me in the beginning when it would have been real easy not to, and never wavering. I sure do love ya, bud. Here’s a few images over the last few years 🤘🏼

I’ve been hunting for 33 years and Tuesday I killed the biggest buck of my life.  I had to make a second shot, rushed it, and scoped myself (worth it) and I’m still not over how shook I was when this joker walked out.  Ironically, hunting has never been about the killing for me. It’s about the friendships, the stories, quiet minutes in the stand, the reverence of the animal, and the opportunity to enjoy God’s creation.  This Mississippi Giant is just the real sweet cherry on top.  I’m real thankful to @mossyoak and their whole team for allowing me and the boys an opportunity to come make memories of a lifetime each year. There’s not a better company and group of people out there  #pawpaw
